## Quick Start

### 1 вЂ” Install dependencies

```bash
cd auth-system
npm install
```

### 2 вЂ” Configure environment

```bash
copy .env.example .env
```

Open `.env` and fill in:

| Variable | What to put |
|---|---|
| `OWNER_USERNAME` | Your dashboard login username |
| `OWNER_PASSWORD` | Your dashboard login password |
| `JWT_SECRET` | Any 64-char random string (run `node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))"`) |
| `SCRIPT_AES_KEY` | 32-char string (run `node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(16).toString('hex'))"`) |
| `PORT` | `3000` or your preferred port |
| `BASE_URL` | Your public URL, e.g. `https://auth.yoursite.com` |
| `DISCORD_TOKEN` | Your bot token from discord.com/developers |
| `DISCORD_GUILD_ID` | Right-click your server в†’ Copy Server ID |
| `DISCORD_CLIENT_ID` | Your bot's client/application ID |
| `DISCORD_OWNER_ROLE_ID` | Role allowed to run owner commands |
| `DISCORD_MEMBER_ROLE_ID` | Role assigned to whitelisted users (optional) |

### 3 вЂ” Copy panel.lua to the frontend folder

```bash
copy roblox\panel.lua frontend\panel.lua
```

Then edit the `API_BASE` line in **both** files to your domain:
```lua
local API_BASE = "https://auth.yoursite.com"
```

### 4 вЂ” Start the server

```bash
npm start
```

Visit `http://localhost:3000` в†’ **Owner Dashboard** в†’ `http://localhost:3000/login.html`

### 5 вЂ” Start the Discord bot (separate terminal)

```bash
npm run bot
```

---

## Discord Bot Commands

| Command | Permission | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `/whitelist-add @user [role]` | Admin | Add user + auto-generate key, DM them |
| `/whitelist-remove @user` | Admin | Delete user permanently |
| `/whitelist-toggle @user true/false` | Admin | Enable / disable access |
| `/whitelist-list` | Admin | Show all active users |
| `/reset-hwid @user` | Admin | Clear their HWID lock |
| `/mykey` | Anyone | DMs you your own key |
| `/setup @user` | Admin | DMs user the panel loadstring |

---

## How Script Delivery Works (Security Model)

```
Owner uploads source code
       в”‚
       в–ј  AES-256-CBC encrypt (server-side key)
   Stored in SQLite (encrypted blob)
       в”‚
       в–ј  User runs panel в†’ enters key
   Panel sends: key + HWID в†’ POST /api/script/fetch
       в”‚
       в–ј  Server:
       в”‚   1. Validates key exists + whitelisted
       в”‚   2. Checks/binds HWID
       в”‚   3. Decrypts source in memory
       в”‚   4. Wraps in base64 + loadstring
       в”‚   5. Returns wrapped script
       в”‚
       в–ј  Source never stored in plain text
          Source never transmitted in plain text
          Each delivery uses a fresh delivery token
```

**The raw Lua source is never accessible to anyone except you (the owner).** Users only ever receive an encrypted, base64-wrapped loadstring that executes in-memory.

---

## Roblox Panel

In your executor, run:

```lua
loadstring(game:HttpGet("https://auth.yoursite.com/panel.lua"))()
```

The panel opens with 4 buttons:

| Button | Action |
|---|---|
| **рџЋ­ Get Role** | Confirms your whitelisted role |
| **рџ“њ Get Script** | Downloads + executes the script (key verified first) |
| **рџ”„ Reset HWID** | Clears your device lock (next launch binds new device) |
| **рџ”‘ My Key** | Copies your key to clipboard |

---

## Deploying to a Server

**Recommended: Railway / Render / VPS**

1. Push the project to a private GitHub repo (never commit `.env`)
2. Set all environment variables in the platform's dashboard
3. Set start command: `node backend/server.js`
4. Update `BASE_URL` and `API_BASE` in `panel.lua` + `frontend/panel.lua`

**HTTPS is strongly recommended** so keys aren't transmitted in plain text.

---

## Security Notes

- `.env` and `data/` are gitignored вЂ” never commit them
- The `SCRIPT_AES_KEY` decrypts all scripts вЂ” keep it secret
- Rate limiting is applied to all API endpoints
- HWID binding prevents key sharing between users
- JWT tokens expire after 12 hours
